Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and set aside.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Put the @dried rosemary{1%sprig}, half the @dried cranberries{15%g}, the @breadcrumbs{10%g} and @water{2%tbsp} into a large #bowl{}.

Add the @British beef mince{240%g} to the bowl. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{} then mix together with your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{25%g} into even circles (about the size of the buns, 1 per person) onto a baking tray lined with #greaseproof paper{}. Bake on the middle shelf until the cheese is golden and crisp around the edges, ~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from the oven and set aside - the cheese will become crisp as it cools.

Meanwhile, in another medium bowl, add the remaining @dried cranberries{15%g}, @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the burgers and fry until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} in total. Carefully turn them every ~{3-4%minutes} and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

As the burgers cook, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Pop a medium #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @creme fraiche{75%g} and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to low and add the cheddar, stirring continuously until fully melted and smooth, ~{2-4%minutes}. Take off the heat and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if too thick.

Cut the @burger buns{2} in half and pop into the oven to warm for ~{2-3%minutes}. When the chips are done, sprinkle with @truffle zest{} and toss to coat.

Just before serving, add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the dressing and toss to coat. Pop the bun bases on your plates and spread with the @onion marmalade{20%g}. Top with a cheese crisp and burger patty then pour cheese sauce all over before closing with the bun lid. Serve with the cranberry salad and truffle chips alongside. Enjoy!